Welcome to the 2020-2021 school year! This is a reminder that all school sites will be offering meal pick-ups only on Mondays and Wednesdays from 11:00am to 1:00pm. Student and school name or LUSD ID number must be presented at the time of pick-up.

It is very important that all students submit a new application for the 2020-2021 school year. Please see a copy of the attached letter that was mailed home July 23, 2020.

Thank you for your continued support.
***
SPANISH
¡Bienvenidos al ciclo escolar 2020-2021!

Este es un recordatorio que todas las escuelas ofrecerán distribución de alimentos solamente los lunes y miércoles de 11:00am a 1:00pm. Se debe presentar el nombre del estudiante y escuela o el número de identificación del estudiante al momento de recoger las comidas.

Es muy importante que someta una nueva aplicación de alimentos para todos los estudiantes para el ciclo escolar 2020-21. Adjunto esta una copia de la carta que fue enviada a casa el 23 de julo, 2020.

Gracias por su apoyo.

post_text: El Distrito Escolar Unificado de Lompoc continúa monitoreando y adaptando sus planes de reapertura de acuerdo a la información más actualizada del Departamento de Salubridad Pública del Condado de Santa Barbara, el Departamento de Educación de California y el Centro para el Control de Enfermedades. La prioridad primordial es la seguridad de nuestros estudiantes y personal. Idealmente, todos los estudiantes regresarían los 5 días a la semana. Sin embargo, debemos cumplir con las guías e indicaciones provistas por el SBCPH y asegurar que los estudiantes y el personal estén seguros al regresar. Basado en las estadísticas más recientes con casos positivos de COVID-19, el LUSD, como otros distritos en California, iniciará el ciclo escolar con el modelo de aprendizaje a distancia. LUSD proporcionará al personal docente oportunidades de desarrollo profesional para que los maestros y estudiantes se sientan apoyados con el aprendizaje a distancia. Las clases reanudarán el 17 de agosto.

post_text: The Lompoc Unified School District continues to monitor and adjust their reopening plans based on the most current information from Santa Barbara County Public Health (SBCPH), California Department of Education, and the Centers for Disease Control. LUSD’s top priority is the safety of our students and staff. Ideally, we would bring all students back five days a week. However, we need to adhere to the guidelines provided by SBCPH and ensure students and staff are safe when they return. Based on the most recent trends with positive COVID-19 cases LUSD, like many other school districts in California, will begin the school year with distance learning. LUSD will be providing staff continuous professional development opportunities so that teachers and students feel supported with distance learning. LUSD students will be returning to school on August 17th. For further information, please visit www.lusd.org for the latest information

text:
The Lompoc Unified School District continues to monitor and adjust their reopening plans based on the most current information from Santa Barbara County Public Health (SBCPH), California Department of Education, and the Centers for Disease Control. LUSD’s top priority is the safety of our students and staff. Ideally, we would bring all students back five days a week. However, we need to adhere to the guidelines provided by SBCPH and ensure students and staff are safe when they return. Based on the most recent trends with positive COVID-19 cases LUSD, like many other school districts in California, will begin the school year with distance learning. LUSD will be providing staff continuous professional development opportunities so that teachers and students feel supported with distance learning. LUSD students will be returning to school on August 17th. For further information, please visit www.lusd.org for the latest information

Get help buying food while schools are closed. #COVID19 Pandemic EBT (P-EBT) benefits will be available for California families with children who are eligible for free or reduced-price meals. Learn more: https://ca.p-ebt.org/info

With schools are closed due to #COVID19, children who are eligible for free or reduced-price meals can get up to $365 in food benefits in addition to community ‘grab-n-go’ meals. Learn more about these food benefits - Pandemic EBT or P-EBT.
https://ca.p-ebt.org/info

#COVID19 Pandemic EBT (P-EBT) benefits will be available for eligible California families soon. Most families with children who get free or reduced-price school meals will get P-EBT cards in the mail soon. Others will need to apply later this month: https://ca.p-ebt.org/info

Margaret Tennant’s former exchange student joined her class this week to talk about school life in China. He discussed life and landmarks in China. He also shared about what it’s like to be a student there including; uniforms, school hours, entrance requirements to be allowed to attend high school.

——

Esta semana, el estudiante de intercambio de Maestra Margaret Tennant participó en su clase para hablar sobre la vida escolar en China. Habló acerca de la vida diaria y los lugares de importancia e históricos. También compartió acerca de lo que es ser un estudiante en ese país incluyendo; uniformes, horario escolar, requisitos para ingresar a la escuela secundaria.

MENSAJE DEL SUPERINTENDENTE DE ESCUELAS TREVOR MCDONALD:

Nos enfrentamos a la incertidumbre en nuestra comunidad, nuestro condado, nuestro estado, nuestra nación y nuestro mundo con respecto al virus COVID-19. Ahora más que nunca, el Distrito Escolar Unificado de Lompoc está al frente guiando a nuestros estudiantes y a las familias durante este tiempo desconocido.

Reconocemos que el cierre de escuelas y todo lo que implica es una carga para todas y cada una de las familias. Queremos que sepa que continuamente trabajamos para identificar formas de brindar actividades educativas significantes a nuestros estudiantes.

Les invitamos a unirse con nosotros y juntos colaborar durante este tiempo. Continuaremos proporcionado recursos para ayudar con la “enseñanza en casa” en nuestra página web www.lusd.org - COVID-19 (https://www.lusd.org/Page/9232)

¡Juntos podemos!

THIS MESSAGE IS BEING SENT ON BEHALF OF SUPERINTENDENT, TREVOR MCDONALD:

We are facing uncertainty in our community, our county, our state, our nation and our world with respect to COVID-19. Now more than ever the Lompoc Unified School District will be at the forefront of leading our kids and families through these uncharted waters.

We recognize the school closures and everything that goes with it are a significant burden to each and every family. We want you to know that we are continuously working to identify ways to deliver meaningful instructional activities to students.

We invite you to be our partner and walk beside us during this time. We will be providing resources to assist with “at-home learning” on our website www.lusd.org- COVID-19 (https://www.lusd.org/Page/9232)

Together, we can!

post_text:
Lompoc Unified School District Schools to close as of Monday, March 16, 2020.

Today, following the recent declaration of a national emergency by our President, the Governor’s Executive Orders, and the growing concerns for our staff and student safety, Lompoc Unified School District has made the extremely difficult decision to close all schools for students beginning Monday, March 16 through Friday, April 3, 2020.

This includes all early learning and adult school activities as well. We will continue to evaluate what is best for our students, staff and community.

We will soon be sending out information on how families can get resources for at-home learning. Grab-n-Go meals will begin on Monday, March 16 at the identified locations as well as:
· The Lompoc Library (on D St)
· El Camino School (on J St.)
· Maple High School
· First Methodist Church (on G St. and North Ave)

Thank you for your patience and understanding.

Trevor McDonald
Superintendent

post_text:
SCHOOL CLOSURE FOOD SERVICES

The Lompoc Unified School District Child Nutrition Services Team will be providing meals, free of charge, to all children 18 & under during the school closure. We will be serving grab-n-go meals that are to be consumed off-site to maintain social distancing. Students are welcome to visit any of the listed sites and do not need to use their student ID. Breakfast will be served from 7:30am-8:30am and lunch will be served from 11:00am-1:00pm at the following sites:

Buena Vista
Clarence Ruth
Crestview
Fillmore
Hapgood
La Cañada
La Honda
Lompoc Valley Middle School
Los Berros

All Child Nutrition Staff has been trained on safe food handling and sanitation procedures and will not report to work if exposed to the virus or showing symptoms of the virus.

We look forward to serving and supporting the community during this difficult time. If you have any questions, please contact Child Nutrition Services at 805-742-3353.

Lompoc Unified School District schools will be closed during the week of February 17-21, 2020 for February Break. The Education Center will be open Wednesday through Friday (February 19 through February 21, 2020).

All LUSD schools will reopen and classes will resume on Monday, February 24, 2020.

Thank you.

______________

Estimados Padres,

Las escuelas del Distrito Escolar Unificado de Lompoc cerraran durante la semana del 17 al 21 de febrero 2020 durante el receso de febrero. Las oficinas del Centro Educativo permanecerán abiertas del miércoles 19 al viernes 21 de febrero 2020.

Todas las escuelas del Distrito Escolar Unificado de Lompoc reanudarán clases el lunes 24 de febrero 2020.

Gracias.

Las escuelas del Distrito Escolar Unificado de Lompoc cerraran durante la semana del 17 al 21 de febrero 2020 durante el receso de febrero. Las oficinas del Centro Educativo permanecerán abiertas del miércoles 19 al viernes 21 de febrero 2020.

Todas las escuelas del Distrito Escolar Unificado de Lompoc reanudarán clases el lunes 24 de febrero 2020.

Gracias.
